<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-12-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-12-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="686" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d686">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-12-17"><hi rend="italic">December 17,
                                    1895</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Repeated demands made for protection everywhere renewed. I think we have
                            no citizens in Zeitoun. Informed by ministry for foreign affairs that
                            160 Turks, male and female, were tortured and killed by Armenians at
                            Zeitoun. * * *</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Terrell.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>